args: Kitty's gone, and I'm all alone.\nJust like last time...
A few years ago, in the arena\nwhere Vanessa grew up...
Heya, Liam! How'd the match go?

Bwa ha ha! Am I seein' things here?
Is a lion-ranked fighter associating with
a TRAINEE? Better be careful, lion,
or his weakness will spread to you!
Cram it, sister! I'll talk to who I want!\n...Wait, Liam? Are you crying AGAIN?
*sniff* M-my match went okay somehow,\nbut only thanks to luck. I...I don't know\nhow much longer I can keep this up!

The fact that a trainee like me is even
alive is already a miracle. So it's like that
woman said—you should leave me before
I end up making you weak.
That's bunk and you know it! Besides,\nyou and me are stray dogs, so it doesn't\nmatter who we hang out with.

Death sneaks up on everybody and clocks
'em over the head, so there's no sense
spending all your time worrying about
when it's gonna happen!
But in the arena, the strong eat the weak.\nThose who are weak either become strong,\nor they no longer become anything at all.
Soon, the time for the test was upon them.

Liam, you pathetic lump'a wasted space!
I've got half a mind to shunt you off to
the mines! 'Least there you might be
able to do somethin' useful for once!
N-no! If you force me away from here,\nI'd have nowhere else to go...
You just run back'n forth and somehow\nmanage not to get killed in the process.\nThere ain't no value in a fighter like that!
Hold up, boss! Sure, he might be a little\non the skittish side, but what if me and\nhim hooked up as a tag team?
Two fighters taking on a huge fiend\nwould be one hell of a show, eh? Ehhhhh?
This is it, Liam! Win this, and you stay.\nRemember, I've got your back!\nYou can do this!

Hell, this is freakin' POINTLESS! Still,
I suppose folks might enjoy watchin' the
two of ya get eaten, so it's your funeral.
...I ain't payin' for a funeral, by the way.
N-no! I can't! This is too much for me!
What, this? This guy's a puppydog!\nJust follow my lead and we've got\nthis thing in the bag!
I...I don't think I can... N-no! I have to!
Vanessa gave me this one chance,\nand I won't let her down! Haaaaah!
Bwa ha ha! Saw that comin' a mile away.\nWhat else'd ya expect, throwin' some\nfool weakling against a fiend like that?
What happened to Liam that day was my fault,\nand it left a dark stain on my heart.\nBut it also taught me something...

If I associate with weak people, they will always
drag me down to their level. It's inevitable.
That's why I'm always seeking out the strongest
people I can possibly find.
I don't even know HOW to associate with\nweaker people anymore. And yet...
Kitty's still gone? *sigh*\nIs there nothing I can do?

I wish we could go back to the way it was
before—when we were still getting along.
But if I were to be overprotective or ask
her to do too much again...
Yeah, this is all a bit over my head.\nMaybe I should ask someone a little\ncloser to her and see what they think.
I bet someone from the Soaratorium\nwill know what to do!
...Wow, that's quite the story there.\nSo basically, because of all that,\nyou wanna know about Felynes?
Yes! Tell me everything! I mean,\nyour world is lousy with 'em, right?
Well, in terms of general traits, most\nFelynes are loyal, obedient, and have\na strong sense of camaraderie.
Okay, good. So how do I deal with 'em?
Oh, come on! You know all about their\nrace and traits and whatever!
Yes, but not every Felyne is the same,\njust like all humans are different.

Agreed! If you wish to work with a specific
Felyne—or even just be friends—you must
sort out your differences one-on-one,
just as you would with anyone else.
You gotta fight for the right to be buds!
...And now, after all that, you have\ndecided to seek my counsel?

Yeah. I mean, we get along despite the
fact I'm weaker than you, so how do you
do it? How can you even stand being
around a pathetic lump like me?
First of all, I would never think of you\nin such a way. Your weakness or strength\nis, frankly, irrelevant to our friendship.
Then allow me a different approach:\nWhy are you going so far to keep your\nFelyne friend around in the first place?
Important how? Because she is a Lynian?\nIf such is the case, your problem can be\nsolved by simply befriending a new Lynian.
This is new, but...sure! Why not?\nLet's be fur-iends.
It's a purr-fectly happy thought,\nVanessa. Thank you, nya!
After all, what kind of Palico would I be\nif I let you do everything!
No. I don't want to be friends with any old\nLynian—I want to be friends with HER.
No one can replace her. She is my one\nand only Lynian in this or any world!
There you have it... What you feel at this\nmoment is what's important—not whether\nshe is weak or strong.
Oh geez, I had this all wrong...
All I've been thinking about is strength.\nBut she's so much more to me...
Your Felyne friend ran off into the\nHoary Woods by herself!
What? She'll be killed on her own!
I need to go save her!
